\f0\fs24 \cf0 Create a complete web application (frontend only) that converts folders of WAV samples into a fully functional SFZ instrument file.\
\
The app must be deployable via GitHub Pages (static site only: HTML, CSS, JavaScript \'97 no backend).\
\
CORE FUNCTIONALITY:\
\
1. File Input\
- Allow users to upload a folder using <input type="file" webkitdirectory multiple>\
- Preserve folder structure via webkitRelativePath\
\
2. Automatic Articulation Detection\
- Each top-level folder inside the selected directory represents one articulation (group)\
- Do NOT rely on folder names like "Normal", "Pizzicato", etc.\
- Detect groups dynamically\
\
3. Keyswitch Assignment\
- Assign keyswitches automatically starting at MIDI note 36 (C2)\
- Each group gets one keyswitch using:\
  sw_lokey=36\
  sw_hikey=48\
  sw_last=<assigned note>\
\
4. Note Detection\
- Extract note names from filenames (e.g., D3, F#4, A#5)\
- Convert to MIDI numbers\
- Ignore files without valid note names\
\
5. Region Mapping (CRITICAL)\
- For each articulation:\
  - Sort samples by pitch\
  - Compute lokey and hikey automatically:\
    - midpoint between adjacent samples\
    - first sample defines lower bound\
    - last sample defines upper bound\
- Assign:\
  pitch_keycenter = original sample MIDI note\
\
6. Path Handling (VERY IMPORTANT)\
- Generate clean relative paths\
- Output must work if SFZ file is placed in root folder with samples\
- Avoid duplicated or broken paths\
- Must support folders with spaces and UTF-8 characters\
\
7. Output\
- Generate valid SFZ text\
- Show preview in <pre>\
- Provide download button that exports "instrument.sfz"\
\
8. UI Requirements\
- Minimal but clear UI:\
  - Folder input\
  - "Generate SFZ" button\
  - Output preview\
  - Error messages if no valid samples found\
- Optional: drag & drop support\
\
9. Code Quality\
- Pure vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)\
- Well structured and commented\
- Separate logic into functions:\
  - note extraction\
  - midi conversion\
  - region building\
  - SFZ generation\
\
10. Edge Cases\
- Ignore files without notes\
- Handle sharps (#)\
- Case-insensitive parsing\
- Avoid crashes if folders are empty\
\
11. Deliverables\
- index.html (single-file app preferred)\
- Clean, readable, production-ready code\
\
EXPECTED RESULT:\
\
The generated SFZ must:\
- Load correctly in Sforzando\
- Trigger articulations via keyswitches\
- Play smoothly across the full detected pitch range\
- Not require manual editing\
\
OPTIONAL (if possible):\
- Display detected articulations in UI\
- Allow reordering articulations (affects keyswitch order)\
\
Do NOT include any backend or Node.js code.\
Do NOT assume specific folder names.\
Do NOT hardcode pitch ranges.\
\
Focus on reliability and correct SFZ output.}